lead_paragraph: The Fed chief said evidence of a rebound was mounting, but did not suggest that a June rate increase was a foregone conclusion.

headline.print_headline: Yellen Sees Rates Rising ‘in the Coming Months’
headline.main: Yellen Says Fed on Track to Raise Rates ‘in Coming Months’

snippet: The Fed chief said evidence of a rebound was mounting, but did not suggest that a June rate increase was a foregone conclusion.
abstract: Federal Reserve chairwoman Janet L Yellen says it will raise its benchmark interest rate 'in the coming months;' says evidence is accumulating that economy is picking up.
